==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Twattle
<hw>Twat"tle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Tattle</er>, <er>Twaddle</er>.]</ety> <def>To prate; to talk much
and idly; to gabble; to chatter; to twaddle; <as>as, a
<ex>twattling</ex> gossip</as>.</def> <rj><au>L'Estrange.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twattle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Twattle
<hw>Twat"tle</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To make much of, as a domestic
animal; to pet.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Grose.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twattle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Twattle
<hw>Twat"tle</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Act of prating; idle talk;
twaddle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twattler</ent>⟦br⟧
